<plot>Like Father, like Son. When a father and son grow tired of their dreary, routine lives, they find solace in the comforting chance that the end of the world may be just around the corner. With the impending apocalypse nigh, and unable to find a reason to live for the present, they ultimately bring on their own fateful future. "When The Day Is Done" is a dark comment on the destructive nature of mundane existence.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?653473</url></doc>
